♪

45
00:02:22,601 --> 00:02:23,649
<i>Dr. Voss,</i>

46
00:02:23,734 --> 00:02:26,789
how would you describe
Logan Kim's performance

47
00:02:26,874 --> 00:02:28,563
as CEO during the pandemic?

48
00:02:28,648 --> 00:02:29,898
Reprehensible.

49
00:02:30,414 --> 00:02:33,930
He tried to coerce our surgeons
to perform elective surgeries

50
00:02:34,015 --> 00:02:36,157
while they were prohibited
for the safety

51
00:02:36,242 --> 00:02:37,688
of staff and patients,

52
00:02:37,773 --> 00:02:39,524
all in the name of
the bottom line.

53
00:02:39,609 --> 00:02:42,117
Logan did everything
he could to keep Chastain afloat.

54
00:02:42,234 --> 00:02:45,479
Unfortunately, not everyone was
willing to follow his lead.

55
00:02:47,861 --> 00:02:49,296
Thank you, Dr. Cain.

56
00:02:49,484 --> 00:02:51,102
I've never thought much
off Logan Kim.

57
00:02:51,187 --> 00:02:52,899
He's a garden-variety
company man.

58
00:02:52,984 --> 00:02:54,624
I don't really have much
to say about him.

59
00:02:58,601 --> 00:03:02,179
Except, when the pandemic hit,
we needed PPE.

60
00:03:02,507 --> 00:03:05,542
He promised he'd bend the rules
to find the money, and he did.

61
00:03:05,867 --> 00:03:07,718
It's the one time
he earned my respect.

62
00:03:12,208 --> 00:03:14,461
- Hey.
- Hey.

63
00:03:14,546 --> 00:03:16,235
- Good to see you, man.
- You, too.

64
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:18,445
- You just get back?
- Yeah.

65
00:03:20,832 --> 00:03:22,398
How was the memorial?

66
00:03:22,976 --> 00:03:26,328
It was sad, but it was nice
to see my relatives.

67
00:03:26,820 --> 00:03:29,023
Now it's time
to move forward.

68
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:32,922
- How's your mom?
- Um, up and down, you know.

69
00:03:33,007 --> 00:03:35,406
But how about you guys?

70
00:03:35,773 --> 00:03:38,446
How was the honeymoon
in, uh, Key West?

71
00:03:38,531 --> 00:03:39,556
It must have been
awesome.

72
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:41,052
Did you waste
away in Margaritaville?

73
00:03:41,136 --> 00:03:41,883
Yes.

74
00:03:41,967 --> 00:03:43,757
Yeah, we did,

75
00:03:43,953 --> 00:03:45,700
- and it was awesome.
- Excuse me. I need some help.

76
00:03:45,784 --> 00:03:48,184
My boss is sick. Please come
outside, it's an emergency.

77
00:03:50,896 --> 00:03:52,610
We were on our way
to a fundraiser,

78
00:03:52,695 --> 00:03:53,948
I insisted we stop.

79
00:03:54,124 --> 00:03:57,703
She's burning up, coughing.
Can't keep anything in her.

80
00:04:01,312 --> 00:04:03,842
Doctors, I have too much
to do today to be sick.

81
00:04:03,926 --> 00:04:07,054
I need you all to work fast
and get me back out there.

82
00:04:07,322 --> 00:04:08,968
Now.

83
00:04:10,916 --> 00:04:12,975
Let's get her into the ER.

84
00:04:21,469 --> 00:04:23,603
Syncopal episode,
incoming to a trauma bay.

85
00:04:23,687 --> 00:04:27,406
Devon,
it's Congresswoman Randall.

86
00:04:27,899 --> 00:04:29,781
♪ ♪

