89
00:04:44,797 --> 00:04:46,549
How long have you had
that pain, Congresswoman?

90
00:04:46,633 --> 00:04:48,250
Please, call me Nichelle.

91
00:04:48,445 --> 00:04:49,470
A few days.

92
00:04:49,555 --> 00:04:51,321
Started with the fevers,
diarrhea.

93
00:04:51,406 --> 00:04:53,851
Which is why you collapsed.
You're severely dehydrated.

94
00:04:53,936 --> 00:04:57,040
Do you think I have a flu,
or is it something I ate?

95
00:04:57,125 --> 00:04:59,079
It's not COVID.
I was vaccinated.

96
00:04:59,164 --> 00:05:01,039
James mentioned a cough
as well.

97
00:05:01,124 --> 00:05:03,235
Anything else we should know?
Underlying conditions

98
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:04,328
you're aware of?

99
00:05:04,412 --> 00:05:05,977
Medications you're currently
taking?

100
00:05:06,062 --> 00:05:08,477
She hugs or shakes hands
with everyone she meets.

101
00:05:08,562 --> 00:05:10,048
And she works too hard.

102
00:05:10,133 --> 00:05:12,281
Because of Governor Wayne's
tragic fishing accident...

103
00:05:12,375 --> 00:05:13,759
May he rest in peace...

104
00:05:13,844 --> 00:05:16,001
I am running in
a special election to be

105
00:05:16,086 --> 00:05:18,063
the first Black female governor
of Georgia.

106
00:05:18,148 --> 00:05:20,509
So, yes,
I hug the people.

107
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:23,774
Push. Push.
Push, push, push. Good.

108
00:05:23,859 --> 00:05:25,665
James, call the office.
I do not want

109
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,351
any of the staff
coming down here.

110
00:05:28,859 --> 00:05:30,571
"Loving mankind is not enough.

111
00:05:30,656 --> 00:05:32,367
You have to love
the individual."

112
00:05:32,570 --> 00:05:33,752
Best speech at the convention.

113
00:05:33,836 --> 00:05:35,625
Thank you.

114
00:05:36,044 --> 00:05:39,095
I hate to interrupt
Dr. Hawkins' fanboy moment,

115
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:40,704
but has there been
any recent travel

116
00:05:40,789 --> 00:05:42,040
not related to the election?

117
00:05:42,125 --> 00:05:44,852
I-I went to a yoga retreat
in Kentucky,

118
00:05:44,937 --> 00:05:47,406
of all places,
along the Ohio River.

119
00:05:48,383 --> 00:05:51,368
Okay. There's a fungal infection
that's common

120
00:05:51,453 --> 00:05:53,282
in that region;
It's called histoplasmosis.

121
00:05:53,367 --> 00:05:55,275
It might explain your symptoms.
We'll look into it.

122
00:05:55,359 --> 00:05:57,549
But don't worry, it's
treatable. We'll send out for cultures,

123
00:05:57,633 --> 00:05:59,337
get you on antibiotics
and antifungals

124
00:05:59,422 --> 00:06:00,648
just to cover our bases.

125
00:06:00,733 --> 00:06:03,704
If it is histo, we'll get you
back on the campaign trail ASAP.

126
00:06:03,789 --> 00:06:05,515
But we are gonna
admit you.

127
00:06:05,956 --> 00:06:07,248
We gotta be safe.

128
00:06:08,054 --> 00:06:10,758
And for the record,
Congresswoman...

129
00:06:10,843 --> 00:06:13,210
Uh-uh. Nichelle.

130
00:06:13,671 --> 00:06:14,687
I insist.

131
00:06:14,772 --> 00:06:16,780
Conrad. I insist.

132
00:06:17,952 --> 00:06:20,835
- Is the congresswoman okay?
- Yeah.

133
00:06:21,108 --> 00:06:22,976
Well, on the off chance
she needs an organ,

134
00:06:23,061 --> 00:06:24,265
I'm happy to donate.

135
00:06:24,349 --> 00:06:26,500
By the way, your husband
over here geeked out on her.

136
00:06:26,585 --> 00:06:27,804
Wow, "husband."

137
00:06:27,889 --> 00:06:29,921
I don't know that
I'll ever get used to that.

138
00:06:30,261 --> 00:06:33,241
And the congresswoman's husband,
Tom Randall,

139
00:06:33,389 --> 00:06:34,696
is at a golf tournament
in Hawaii.

140
00:06:34,780 --> 00:06:35,902
He won't be here
until tomorrow.

141
00:06:35,986 --> 00:06:40,359
Ooh, Tom Randall is my top
fantasy dinner party invite.

142
00:06:40,444 --> 00:06:42,929
Falcons' greatest quarterback,
Hall of Famer.

143
00:06:43,014 --> 00:06:46,125
Denied a Super Bowl victory
by the worst call in history.

144
00:06:46,210 --> 00:06:48,748
Wow, you are a big
Tom Randall groupie, huh?

145
00:06:50,154 --> 00:06:51,978
Everything will be ready
in about five minutes.

146
00:06:52,062 --> 00:06:53,222
Meet you guys down there.

147
00:07:02,975 --> 00:07:05,483
- You stabbed me in the back.
- I told the truth.

148
00:07:06,662 --> 00:07:08,390
The truth you knew
would get me fired.

149
00:07:08,475 --> 00:07:10,695
No. I told them
you did a good thing.

150
00:07:10,780 --> 00:07:12,304
You listened to your
better angels

151
00:07:12,389 --> 00:07:14,952
when you got us that PPE,
so I appealed to theirs.

152
00:07:15,062 --> 00:07:16,359
Well, you're gonna find yourself

153
00:07:16,444 --> 00:07:17,876
- incredibly disappointed.
- Let me explain something to you.

154
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:20,726
I know what I stand for.
I know what I'm fighting for.

155
00:07:20,811 --> 00:07:22,640
You could have actually
done some good here.

156
00:07:22,725 --> 00:07:24,100
You could have stood
with me.

157
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:27,867
But you let Red Rock infect you.
So I did you a favor today.

158
00:07:27,952 --> 00:07:29,593
I saved you
from a disease.

159
00:07:29,999 --> 00:07:33,093
Getting fired can be
a beautiful thing, trust me.

160
00:07:34,085 --> 00:07:36,146
Now you and I have that
in common.

161
00:07:37,577 --> 00:07:38,780
Hey.

162
00:07:41,108 --> 00:07:44,821
Hang on tight, Dr. Hawkins.
It's going to get...

163
00:07:45,389 --> 00:07:47,824
even uglier around here.

164
00:07:48,679 --> 00:07:49,867
Trust me.

165
00:08:01,482 --> 00:08:04,936
These were our
colleagues and our friends.

166
00:08:06,061 --> 00:08:09,850
Health care workers who died
in the line of duty from COVID.

167
00:08:11,381 --> 00:08:13,733
I hope we never have to
put another face

168
00:08:14,296 --> 00:08:16,819
or name on this memorial.

169
00:08:26,483 --> 00:08:27,953
You know,
I was with Nurse Garner

170
00:08:28,038 --> 00:08:29,242
when he passed away.

171
00:08:29,327 --> 00:08:32,226
Heartbreaking.
Such a lovely man.

172
00:08:32,311 --> 00:08:36,570
I-I had to go out and tell
his enormous entourage...

173
00:08:36,655 --> 00:08:40,968
Wife, kids, parents,
siblings, friends... I...

174
00:08:41,491 --> 00:08:43,819
It's a life cut short
but certainly well-lived.

175
00:08:44,186 --> 00:08:46,452
And you know, I don't know
if I was...

176
00:08:46,749 --> 00:08:49,921
if I was feeling envy or...
or jealousy,

177
00:08:50,069 --> 00:08:53,436
but I-I mean, I just,
I have to admit I...

178
00:08:54,209 --> 00:08:56,444
I wish I had even a small part
of what he had.

179
00:08:56,647 --> 00:08:59,867
In the very distant future,
when you're on your deathbed,

180
00:08:59,952 --> 00:09:02,500
I and every one
of your friends here

181
00:09:02,585 --> 00:09:04,264
who you haven't outlived...

182
00:09:04,349 --> 00:09:05,921
will be at your bedside.

183
00:09:06,069 --> 00:09:07,679
Well, I appreciate it.

184
00:09:08,515 --> 00:09:11,210
I've just come to regret some of
the bridges I've burned,

185
00:09:11,327 --> 00:09:12,876
the people I've hurt,
that's all.

186
00:09:12,961 --> 00:09:14,827
Figure out who's worth
fighting for

187
00:09:14,912 --> 00:09:17,773
to get back in your life
and get after it already.

188
00:09:25,375 --> 00:09:26,751
Sat's 85.

189
00:09:26,836 --> 00:09:28,421
You're not getting enough
oxygen. We need you

190
00:09:28,476 --> 00:09:29,327
- off the phone...
- Senator Buxton,

191
00:09:29,411 --> 00:09:30,312
I'd like to put you
on the phone

192
00:09:30,397 --> 00:09:32,321
with one of your constituents.
Her name is Bianca.

193
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:35,694
She is a hardworking young woman
who can't afford childcare.

194
00:09:35,779 --> 00:09:37,272
Yeah, tell her what you just
told me.

195
00:09:38,062 --> 00:09:39,281
Sat's down to 83.

196
00:09:39,366 --> 00:09:40,609
Nichelle!

197
00:09:42,698 --> 00:09:44,015
I don't feel right.

198
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:47,241
What's happening?

199
00:09:51,430 --> 00:09:53,181
Devon?

200
00:09:53,632 --> 00:09:54,936
Devon.

201
00:09:55,020 --> 00:09:57,234
Devon, give me the mask.

202
00:10:00,070 --> 00:10:01,833
Let's get another X-ray, okay?

203
00:10:01,918 --> 00:10:04,687
She's a little wheezy.
How about some nebs?

204
00:10:18,116 --> 00:10:21,413
Mr. Mullins here came in with a
few weeks of worsening dyspnea.

205
00:10:21,498 --> 00:10:22,790
And look at this.

206
00:10:24,881 --> 00:10:27,905
Right axis deviation.
Right heart strain pattern.

207
00:10:27,990 --> 00:10:30,937
And evidence of pulmonary
hypertension on bedside echo.

208
00:10:31,163 --> 00:10:32,649
Also complained of
some dizziness,

209
00:10:32,734 --> 00:10:35,054
so I sent him through
the answer box, which...

210
00:10:35,889 --> 00:10:38,468
Fine. CT scanner.

211
00:10:39,648 --> 00:10:42,125
His head CT revealed
some old ischemic strokes.

212
00:10:42,210 --> 00:10:44,727
But the reason
I called you is...

213
00:10:44,913 --> 00:10:47,822
Proximal filling
defects in the pulmonary artery.

214
00:10:47,906 --> 00:10:49,565
It's consistent with
thromboembolic

215
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:50,807
pulmonary hypertension.

216
00:10:50,891 --> 00:10:53,688
- Uh, what's that?
- Uh, blood clots

217
00:10:53,773 --> 00:10:55,501
in the artery that leads
from your heart to your lungs.

218
00:10:55,585 --> 00:10:57,103
That's why you're
having trouble breathing.

219
00:10:57,187 --> 00:10:58,391
Based on these images,

220
00:10:58,476 --> 00:11:00,031
these clots could be
a few months old.

221
00:11:00,116 --> 00:11:01,728
They could
have started last April.

222
00:11:01,812 --> 00:11:03,862
That's when he had an urgent
spine surgery here

223
00:11:03,946 --> 00:11:05,581
followed by COVID-19.

224
00:11:06,318 --> 00:11:08,107
Oh. This sounds bad.

225
00:11:08,192 --> 00:11:09,780
What happens now?

226
00:11:09,999 --> 00:11:12,930
Well, based on your husband's
hemodynamic instability,

227
00:11:13,015 --> 00:11:15,349
we should plan for surgery
to remove the clots as soon

228
00:11:15,433 --> 00:11:16,953
as possible.
Then he'll be able

229
00:11:17,038 --> 00:11:18,851
to breathe comfortably again.

230
00:11:23,976 --> 00:11:25,184
I knew he looked familiar.

231
00:11:25,276 --> 00:11:28,352
I butted heads with Cain
months ago over this guy.

232
00:11:28,437 --> 00:11:31,460
He reclassified his elective
spine surgery as urgent.

233
00:11:31,663 --> 00:11:33,689
Which means if Mullins got COVID
here at Chastain...

234
00:11:33,773 --> 00:11:35,312
He's another Cain casualty.

235
00:11:35,397 --> 00:11:37,252
And we both know that that
surgery wasn't truly emergent.

236
00:11:37,336 --> 00:11:39,517
Well, we suspect.
We don't know for sure.

237
00:11:39,602 --> 00:11:40,791
Okay, in Mina's kangaroo court,

238
00:11:40,875 --> 00:11:42,461
Barrett Cain is sentenced
to death.

239
00:11:42,688 --> 00:11:45,009
All right, I'm gonna
find out for sure.

240
00:11:58,688 --> 00:12:01,243
- You okay?
- Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

241
00:12:01,328 --> 00:12:03,251
You froze up before,
and then you took off

242
00:12:03,336 --> 00:12:05,090
like a bat out of hell.

243
00:12:05,174 --> 00:12:07,868
Yeah, I'm just fried.
It's jet lag.

244
00:12:13,039 --> 00:12:14,432
Multiple small nodules

245
00:12:14,516 --> 00:12:16,744
with surrounding
ground glass opacities.

246
00:12:16,828 --> 00:12:18,654
It's consistent
with histoplasmosis.

247
00:12:18,738 --> 00:12:20,696
And a lot of other types
