00:25:25,067 --> 00:25:26,881
but you will be held responsible
for this.

496
00:25:27,113 --> 00:25:29,294
Logan Kim isn't here
to protect you anymore.

497
00:25:29,512 --> 00:25:30,779
Hey.

498
00:25:30,895 --> 00:25:33,380
Let's just, uh,
take a breath, all right?

499
00:25:38,981 --> 00:25:41,013
He had a stroke in his
nondominant frontal lobe.

500
00:25:41,098 --> 00:25:42,395
All right.

501
00:25:42,559 --> 00:25:44,989
Well, looks like we can
proceed with the surgery.

502
00:25:45,216 --> 00:25:47,295
The blood thinners he's on
should be adequate

503
00:25:47,380 --> 00:25:50,146
to treat the clot,
but we need you to be on standby

504
00:25:50,231 --> 00:25:51,888
in case there's
hemorrhagic transformation

505
00:25:51,973 --> 00:25:53,722
and the vessel bursts.

506
00:25:54,216 --> 00:25:55,770
Always here
when you need me.

507
00:25:56,657 --> 00:25:58,762
You'd both do well
to remember that.

508
00:26:16,569 --> 00:26:18,012
Dr. Voss?

509
00:26:21,848 --> 00:26:23,844
Kit, what's going on down there?

510
00:26:23,959 --> 00:26:25,843
Better if I show you.

511
00:26:35,700 --> 00:26:37,271
Nichelle has something
on her skin

512
00:26:37,356 --> 00:26:38,864
that looks like shingles.

513
00:26:39,317 --> 00:26:40,864
You have shingles, too.

514
00:26:41,122 --> 00:26:44,701
- Why?
- I don't know. Coincidence?

515
00:26:44,786 --> 00:26:46,920
It's a symptom of something
you and Nichelle caught

516
00:26:47,005 --> 00:26:48,623
when you were
out of town together.

517
00:26:48,708 --> 00:26:51,115
- I'm guessing nowhere near Kentucky.
- I'm her driver.

518
00:26:51,317 --> 00:26:52,935
- All right? That's all.
- Yeah, no, of course.

519
00:26:53,019 --> 00:26:56,060
That being said, she's gonna die
unless I get the truth.

520
00:27:02,114 --> 00:27:03,770
We were in the Caribbean.

521
00:27:04,614 --> 00:27:05,778
Jamaica.

522
00:27:07,684 --> 00:27:10,045
Are the meds you're taking
for the shingles working?

523
00:27:10,130 --> 00:27:11,536
Not really. Why?

524
00:27:11,621 --> 00:27:14,442
Because I know what you both
have now, and it's not shingles.

525
00:27:32,613 --> 00:27:34,810
All right.

526
00:27:34,895 --> 00:27:37,653
A massive clot removed
and a beating heart.

527
00:27:37,794 --> 00:27:40,176
I say it's a beautiful day
in the OR.

528
00:27:41,914 --> 00:27:43,424
Intracranial pressure

529
00:27:43,508 --> 00:27:44,641
is rising.

530
00:27:49,676 --> 00:27:51,616
- Pupils are blown.
- He's brain-hemorrhaging.

531
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:53,670
And herniating.
He doesn't have much time.

532
00:27:53,755 --> 00:27:56,818
- Somebody call Cain.
- He's already here.

533
00:27:56,903 --> 00:27:58,067
Elevate the head,

534
00:27:58,152 --> 00:28:00,723
reverse the blood thinners,
prep for a craniotomy.

535
00:28:14,110 --> 00:28:15,364
Incision.

536
00:28:25,785 --> 00:28:27,373
Intracranial
pressure is up to 60.

537
00:28:27,458 --> 00:28:28,615
I know how high it is.

538
00:28:28,700 --> 00:28:30,458
Ready to enter the skull. Drill?

539
00:29:07,051 --> 00:29:08,474
Blood pressure's rising fast.

540
00:29:08,559 --> 00:29:09,677
What's going
on up there, Cain?

541
00:29:09,761 --> 00:29:11,155
I stopped the bleed,
but he's still herniating.

542
00:29:11,239 --> 00:29:12,467
- How is that possible?
- He's bleeding

543
00:29:12,551 --> 00:29:13,973
from a place where I can't see.

544
00:29:14,137 --> 00:29:15,653
Other side of the brain.

545
00:29:15,770 --> 00:29:17,233
- Ultrasound?
- Aren't you supposed

546
00:29:17,317 --> 00:29:18,999
to drill a hole
in the other side of the skull?

547
00:29:19,083 --> 00:29:21,355
No, he doesn't have
the time for two craniotomies.

548
00:29:21,439 --> 00:29:23,132
I'm gonna pass the needle
from this side of the brain

549
00:29:23,216 --> 00:29:24,525
to the other
to remove the blood.

550
00:29:24,676 --> 00:29:26,476
You can't blindly poke
a needle through the sides

551
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:28,937
- of his brain. You'll kill him.
- I don't blindly operate,

552
00:29:29,021 --> 00:29:31,161
and nobody asked
for your permission.

553
00:29:33,058 --> 00:29:34,736
Yo, have you ever
done this before?

554
00:29:34,821 --> 00:29:36,403
Nope. Never.

555
00:29:39,623 --> 00:29:41,020
We need to stop this.

556
00:29:41,105 --> 00:29:43,147
If we do, the patient will die.

557
00:29:43,536 --> 00:29:45,310
Listen to your mentor, Okafor.

558
00:29:45,395 --> 00:29:46,997
Stay in your lane.

559
00:29:49,583 --> 00:29:51,325
Blood pressure's dropping.

560
00:29:51,448 --> 00:29:53,248
Time to go to work.

561
00:30:11,825 --> 00:30:12,981
BP stabilized.

562
00:30:31,091 --> 00:30:32,989
You're going to protect Cain.

563
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:35,926
He's done so much harm.

564
00:30:36,011 --> 00:30:38,506
Yeah, but in his mind, he's just
doing whatever he can do

565
00:30:38,591 --> 00:30:40,884
to survive in a system
that's been rigged against us.

566
00:30:40,968 --> 00:30:45,439
So you think systemic racism
excuses his behavior?

567
00:30:45,825 --> 00:30:47,161
No.

568
00:30:47,403 --> 00:30:49,106
But it does explain it.

569
00:30:50,630 --> 00:30:54,357
The frustration,
the-the pain, the anger

570
00:30:54,442 --> 00:30:56,763
that builds up,
knowing that in this country,

571
00:30:56,848 --> 00:30:59,069
your life can go south
at any moment

572
00:30:59,154 --> 00:31:02,339
just because of the melanin
in your skin.

573
00:31:03,422 --> 00:31:05,617
Now, I was raised not
to let the unfairness

574
00:31:05,702 --> 00:31:08,200
of discrimination consume me.

575
00:31:08,285 --> 00:31:09,985
But if Cain wasn't taught that,

576
00:31:10,070 --> 00:31:12,161
can you blame him
for how he turned out?

577
00:31:12,246 --> 00:31:14,216
I mean, what else do you expect?

578
00:31:14,919 --> 00:31:16,333
I wasn't born in this country,

579
00:31:16,418 --> 00:31:19,348
so my experience and history
with racism is different,

580
00:31:19,433 --> 00:31:21,517
but this is
a mistake.

581
00:31:21,824 --> 00:31:24,302
I believe
Cain can be redeemed.

582
00:31:24,473 --> 00:31:27,255
You're wrong.
People don't change.

583
00:31:28,372 --> 00:31:30,692
Okay, well,
here's the bottom line.

584
00:31:30,777 --> 00:31:32,811
I've listened
to your input, Mina,

585
00:31:32,896 --> 00:31:34,419
but at the end of the day,

586
00:31:34,535 --> 00:31:37,153
it's my decision
whether to report him or not.

587
00:31:37,934 --> 00:31:39,332
Not yours.

588
00:31:39,536 --> 00:31:42,059
And I need you to respect that.

589
00:31:42,614 --> 00:31:47,239
Are you asking me as m...
As my colleague or my boyfriend?

590
00:31:49,598 --> 00:31:52,816
- Does it matter?
- What you do matters to me.

591
00:31:59,747 --> 00:32:02,484
- How did it go with Jake?
<i>- Not well.</i>

592
00:32:02,568 --> 00:32:04,486
- Oh, I'm sorry, Randolph.
<i>- You know, I've always</i>

593
00:32:04,570 --> 00:32:06,770
felt guilty about leaving him.

594
00:32:06,855 --> 00:32:10,033
And...
He needed a father.

595
00:32:10,316 --> 00:32:13,902
<i>And I'm not so sure
about the choices he's made.</i>

596
00:32:13,987 --> 00:32:15,825
- Can you do anything about it?
<i>- No, he's...</i>

597
00:32:15,910 --> 00:32:18,028
He's a grown man, he's moved on.

598
00:32:18,609 --> 00:32:23,029
And I think my chance to have
any positive impact on him

599
00:32:23,153 --> 00:32:24,738
- has passed me by.
<i>- You can't give up</i>

600
00:32:24,823 --> 00:32:26,114
<i>so easily, Randolph.</i>

601
00:32:26,199 --> 00:32:27,524
Put up a fight.

602
00:32:27,872 --> 00:32:29,344
Oh, I have to hang up.

603
00:32:30,036 --> 00:32:32,630
It's time to ambush
the CEO of Red Rock.

604
00:32:32,731 --> 00:32:34,908
<i>- What?</i>
- And your lunch

605
00:32:34,993 --> 00:32:37,926
is at 12:30 and...
Sir, I'll call security.

606
00:32:38,091 --> 00:32:40,891
It's okay. Dr. Voss
isn't here to hurt me.

607
00:32:41,202 --> 00:32:42,694
Although, given her mastery
of the spine,

608
00:32:42,778 --> 00:32:44,301
I'm sure she could.

609
00:32:44,560 --> 00:32:46,904
Listen, I'm sorry you got
the cold shoulder all day,

610
00:32:46,989 --> 00:32:49,208
but my assistant,
she's a bit overprotective.

611
00:32:49,293 --> 00:32:51,854
All will be forgiven
if you answer one question:

612
00:32:52,031 --> 00:32:54,481
Who's replacing
Logan Kim as CEO?

613
00:32:56,077 --> 00:32:57,971
Chastain isn't
getting a new CEO.

614
00:32:58,056 --> 00:32:59,732
I don't understand.
Someone has to be in charge.

615
00:32:59,816 --> 00:33:01,778
Who's gonna
run the hospital?

616
00:33:05,842 --> 00:33:07,051
<i>Dr. Voss expects</i>

617
00:33:07,136 --> 00:33:08,926
you'll be up
and walking again soon.

618
00:33:09,011 --> 00:33:10,403
She said I had lesions
on my spine.

619
00:33:10,488 --> 00:33:11,903
Please tell me you
know what I have.

620
00:33:11,988 --> 00:33:12,771
We do.

621
00:33:12,856 --> 00:33:15,012
You have a parasitic worm
called a Schistosoma.

622
00:33:15,097 --> 00:33:17,533
And your spinal lesion biopsy
confirmed it.

623
00:33:17,618 --> 00:33:19,317
They're usually found in places

624
00:33:19,402 --> 00:33:24,020
like the Middle East,
Southeast Asia, the Caribbean.

625
00:33:25,215 --> 00:33:26,301
The Caribbean?

626
00:33:26,386 --> 00:33:27,748
Do you have any idea
how lucky you are

627
00:33:27,832 --> 00:33:29,700
that we had the time
and the patience

628
00:33:29,793 --> 00:33:31,575
to figure out
what was going wrong with you

629
00:33:31,660 --> 00:33:33,128
before your organs failed,
despite...

630
00:33:33,213 --> 00:33:34,556
- Devon.
- No, no, no.

631
00:33:34,641 --> 00:33:35,989
She needs to hear this.

632
00:33:36,418 --> 00:33:37,747
You lied to us.

633
00:33:37,949 --> 00:33:40,511
We have sick people out there
who need our attention,

634
00:33:40,596 --> 00:33:42,589
but we were stuck here wading
through your nonsense.

635
00:33:42,673 --> 00:33:43,926
Let me talk to her.

636
00:33:51,701 --> 00:33:54,606
We put you on antiparasitics
for the next four weeks.

637
00:33:54,950 --> 00:33:56,770
James is on them, too.

638
00:34:05,632 --> 00:34:08,255
Keeping secrets from
your doctors can kill you.

639
00:34:08,340 --> 00:34:10,506
I don't want you to think
I'm just another politician

640
00:34:10,591 --> 00:34:11,426
who had an affair.

641
00:34:11,511 --> 00:34:13,045
- I am not here to judge you.
- Well, that's what

642
00:34:13,129 --> 00:34:15,381
people do unless
you give them context.

643
00:34:16,411 --> 00:34:18,954
You know, I represent
the district I grew up in

644
00:34:19,038 --> 00:34:20,038
in Atlanta.

645
00:34:20,364 --> 00:34:21,623
I love my people.

646
00:34:21,707 --> 00:34:23,533
And I've been able to
make a difference where change

647
00:34:23,617 --> 00:34:24,895
is hard to come by.

648
00:34:25,801 --> 00:34:28,129
At first,
my husband understood that.

649
00:34:28,247 --> 00:34:30,443
When we met,
he was an NFL megastar

650
00:34:30,528 --> 00:34:32,801
and I was a judge
in small-claims court.

651
00:34:33,333 --> 00:34:35,223
Now no one asks him
about football.

652
00:34:35,308 --> 00:34:38,044
They ask him what it's like
to be married to me.

653
00:34:38,277 --> 00:34:40,708
And his ego
can't handle that.

654
00:34:42,079 --> 00:34:43,669
But James...

655
00:34:44,286 --> 00:34:45,708
Yeah?

656
00:34:45,972 --> 00:34:48,716
He'd love to tell people what
it's like to be married to you.

657
00:34:50,718 --> 00:34:51,987
Yes, sir.

658
00:34:52,419 --> 00:34:54,137
He's a good man, my James.

659
00:34:55,265 --> 00:34:57,684
While my husband might not
sleep with me anymore,

660
00:34:57,769 --> 00:34:59,211
but he will do
a press conference tomorrow

661
00:34:59,295 --> 00:35:01,638
and say, "My wife is stronger
than half the men

662
00:35:01,723 --> 00:35:04,098
I played football with.
No bug's gonna stop her."

663
00:35:04,257 --> 00:35:07,843
But if I was outed as unfaithful
to Atlanta's favorite son,

664
00:35:07,928 --> 00:35:09,989
I would never make it
to the governor's mansion.

665
00:35:10,074 --> 00:35:11,467
You know we're duty bound
to keep

666
00:35:11,552 --> 00:35:12,994
your personal life
confidential.

667
00:35:13,079 --> 00:35:14,547
I know.

668
00:35:14,835 --> 00:35:18,348
But it will get out eventually.

669
00:35:27,844 --> 00:35:29,825
Can you ask James to
come in here?

670
00:35:45,801 --> 00:35:47,130
She almost died
keeping a secret.

671
00:35:47,287 --> 00:35:48,887
Anything you want to tell me?

672
00:35:54,118 --> 00:35:56,203
After the memorial,
I went to the hospital

673
00:35:56,288 --> 00:35:57,614
where my dad died.

674
00:35:57,699 --> 00:35:59,583
I found the resident
that took care of him.

675
00:36:00,456 --> 00:36:04,267
It was a good guy,
reminded me of you actually.

676
00:36:07,670 --> 00:36:10,653
They were understaffed,
too few vents.

677
00:36:10,931 --> 00:36:13,108
One nurse for every
ten patients.

678
00:36:13,193 --> 00:36:14,902
We have one nurse
for every two patients.

679
00:36:14,987 --> 00:36:16,583
They intubated him.

680
00:36:16,668 --> 00:36:19,294
He was stable until,
like, 2:00 a.m.

681
00:36:19,379 --> 00:36:22,387
His sat dropped,
heart rate started to slow.

682
00:36:22,472 --> 00:36:23,739
Ten minutes went by.

683
00:36:23,824 --> 00:36:25,909
And when they finally
got to him, he was gone.

684
00:36:25,994 --> 00:36:27,497
Cardiac arrest.

685
00:36:28,258 --> 00:36:30,585
My father, he died alone

686
00:36:30,722 --> 00:36:33,140
because his public hospital,
in a poor brown neighborhood,

687
00:36:33,225 --> 00:36:35,389
didn't have enough resources
to save him.

688
00:36:37,132 --> 00:36:38,929
I'm so, so sorry, man.

689
00:36:53,920 --> 00:36:56,593
When the,
when the resident was...

690
00:36:59,554 --> 00:37:01,530
When he was rereading his notes,

691
00:37:03,983 --> 00:37:05,662
he started to cry.

692
00:37:05,746 --> 00:37:07,046
And I said to him,

693
00:37:07,568 --> 00:37:10,568
"Hey, l-look, we all have
that patient we know

694
00:37:10,653 --> 00:37:12,929
we could have saved."

695
00:37:13,014 --> 00:37:14,495
And he said to me,

696
00:37:16,364 --> 00:37:18,768
"If only it had just been one."

697
00:37:19,774 --> 00:37:20,971
There had been dozens.

698
00:37:31,254 --> 00:37:35,316
We'll continue to monitor him
but, uh, his prognosis is good.

699
00:37:35,400 --> 00:37:38,561
Dr. Cain said the same thing.

700
00:37:38,885 --> 00:37:40,403
He stopped by.

701
00:37:41,243 --> 00:37:43,807
His words were
such a comfort.

702
00:37:45,734 --> 00:37:50,346
We are indebted to him, to all
of you, for saving Ben's life.

703
00:37:55,037 --> 00:37:57,596
Mrs. Mullins, there's something
you should know.

704
00:38:09,124 --> 00:38:12,143
You went behind my back
and told the Mullins about Cain.

705
00:38:12,339 --> 00:38:14,424
- I explicitly told you not to.
- Oh.

706
00:38:14,509 --> 00:38:15,565
Now they're suing.

707
00:38:15,650 --> 00:38:16,949
You weren't listening to reason.

708
00:38:17,034 --> 00:38:18,487
I was listening to my gut.

709
00:38:18,622 --> 00:38:20,893
Which tells me to believe
in Cain's redemption.

710
00:38:20,978 --> 00:38:22,316
You don't get to override that,
Mina.

711
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:24,365
Barrett Cain broke the first
tenet of our profession,

712
00:38:24,449 --> 00:38:25,838
"do no harm."

713
00:38:25,923 --> 00:38:27,300
He shouldn't be allowed
to practice medicine.

714
00:38:27,384 --> 00:38:29,823
I did you a favor.
I did us all a favor.

715
00:38:29,908 --> 00:38:31,609
You didn't do anybody
a favor.

716
00:38:31,876 --> 00:38:33,436
You just carried out
your own verdict

717
00:38:33,521 --> 00:38:35,068
in Mina's kangaroo court.

718
00:38:35,153 --> 00:38:37,129
And you
disrespected me.

719
00:38:39,476 --> 00:38:41,713
If you're looking for me
to apologize,

720
00:38:42,909 --> 00:38:44,597
that's not happening.

721
00:38:46,138 --> 00:38:48,651
You know, by my count,
it's been nine

722
00:38:48,736 --> 00:38:51,612
consecutive nights of
soul-stirring sex

723
00:38:51,697 --> 00:38:53,612
- and unparalleled conversation.
- Mm.

724
00:38:53,697 --> 00:38:55,791
And, though I will deny
ever saying this,

725
00:38:55,971 --> 00:38:57,461
my back hurts.

726
00:38:57,632 --> 00:38:58,824
Are you suggesting
we take a break?

727
00:38:58,908 --> 00:39:01,201
- Yes.
- Agreed.

728
00:39:01,854 --> 00:39:02,924
Two nights.

729
00:39:03,016 --> 00:39:04,366
Three.

730
00:39:06,395 --> 00:39:07,495
Agreed.

731
00:39:07,580 --> 00:39:10,690
Rest your back
and reconsider your actions.

732
00:39:11,052 --> 00:39:13,713
Yeah.
And you reconsider, too.

733
00:39:24,666 --> 00:39:26,205
New driver, huh?

734
00:39:28,346 --> 00:39:30,416
Can't move forward
without change.

735
00:39:31,780 --> 00:39:33,416
But good news.

736
00:39:33,518 --> 00:39:36,291
Senator Buxton freed up
some federal money

737
00:39:36,376 --> 00:39:39,295
for our childcare needs,
so not a bad day's work.

738
00:39:39,549 --> 00:39:41,002
I'll mention that to Bianca.

739
00:39:41,203 --> 00:39:43,409
Trust me, somewhere
in Atlanta there is a girl

740
00:39:43,494 --> 00:39:44,894
named Bianca with two kids

741
00:39:44,979 --> 00:39:47,038
who can't afford
to take care of them.

742
00:39:49,243 --> 00:39:52,073
Thank you for everything.

743
00:39:53,389 --> 00:39:55,182
Best of luck to you, Conrad.

744
00:39:58,573 --> 00:40:00,752
Best of luck to you, Nichelle.

745
00:40:09,080 --> 00:40:10,953
Oh, what the hell, man?

746
00:40:11,038 --> 00:40:12,901
How do you go from absent
ex-stepfather

747
00:40:12,986 --> 00:40:14,096
to shameless groupie...

748
00:40:14,181 --> 00:40:15,519
I'm here because
I want to be here,

749
00:40:15,603 --> 00:40:17,276
and because there's something
I need to say to you.

750
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:19,663
You needed a father,
and I dropped the ball.

751
00:40:19,748 --> 00:40:21,832
You're a very
talented musician.

752
00:40:21,917 --> 00:40:23,016
- Thanks.
- You know,

753
00:40:23,101 --> 00:40:25,301
having said that, I know
it's-it's hard to make a living

754
00:40:25,410 --> 00:40:27,587
in the music business no matter...

755
00:40:27,672 --> 00:40:29,832
- without a lot of luck.
- Okay, this is priceless.

756
00:40:29,917 --> 00:40:31,611
You know, I don't know how you
supplement your passion,

757
00:40:31,695 --> 00:40:33,766
but I'd... I would like to help.

758
00:40:33,851 --> 00:40:35,587
The thing is,
I don't need your help.

759
00:40:35,932 --> 00:40:38,829
I play music to relieve stress.
I'm a surgeon.

760
00:40:40,226 --> 00:40:41,876
Plastics and ENT.

761
00:40:44,407 --> 00:40:45,806
I...

762
00:40:45,891 --> 00:40:46,946
I googled you.

763
00:40:47,031 --> 00:40:48,493
I use Wong,
my mother's maiden name,

764
00:40:48,578 --> 00:40:49,633
for my medical practice.

765
00:40:49,718 --> 00:40:52,782
She is the one who put me
through medical school.

766
00:40:56,249 --> 00:40:57,834
Don't do that.

767
00:40:58,008 --> 00:40:59,876
- What?
- Smile

768
00:40:59,961 --> 00:41:03,344
like you had any influence on
my decision to go into medicine.

769
00:41:13,069 --> 00:41:15,290
I'm glad Devon finally
opened up to you.

770
00:41:15,848 --> 00:41:16,930
You're a good friend.

771
00:41:17,043 --> 00:41:19,494
Oh, it's devastating.

772
00:41:19,579 --> 00:41:21,844
- I hate that he's going through this.
- Mm.

773
00:41:22,958 --> 00:41:26,688
Promise me,
let's never run for office.

774
00:41:26,775 --> 00:41:30,329
Or become sports icons.

775
00:41:32,045 --> 00:41:34,679
And let's never, ever
keep secrets from each other.

776
00:41:35,824 --> 00:41:39,278
Right. No. Never.

777
00:41:42,314 --> 00:41:45,975
What is it?
You look adorably insane.

778
00:41:46,457 --> 00:41:48,927
Well, in the spirit
of excellent rules

779
00:41:49,011 --> 00:41:50,801
for a healthy marriage,

780
00:41:51,220 --> 00:41:54,434
there's something
I have to tell you.

781
00:41:55,827 --> 00:41:57,129
Okay.

782
00:42:04,281 --> 00:42:05,692
I'm pregnant.

783
00:42:08,030 --> 00:42:09,506
What? How?

784
00:42:10,842 --> 00:42:11,989
Four years of medical school

785
00:42:12,074 --> 00:42:13,216
and you still don't know
how this works?

786
00:42:13,300 --> 00:42:14,622
I didn't know
we pulled the goalie.

787
00:42:14,706 --> 00:42:17,223
We didn't. I know.
It's-it's...

788
00:42:17,999 --> 00:42:19,450
it's crazy.

789
00:42:20,108 --> 00:42:24,153
♪ <i>If you wake up</i>
<i>without any reason</i> ♪

790
00:42:24,363 --> 00:42:25,793
Holy crap.

791
00:42:26,918 --> 00:42:28,247
Yeah.

792
00:42:28,332 --> 00:42:31,710
♪ <i>Late at night</i>
<i>and I'm not there</i> ♪

793
00:42:32,013 --> 00:42:34,282
Oh, my God, you are gonna
be the best mother ever.

794
00:42:36,037 --> 00:42:39,671
And you're gonna be
the best dad.

795
00:42:42,374 --> 00:42:44,749
You are gonna be the kind
of mother who makes sure

796
00:42:44,834 --> 00:42:46,961
her kids have an even better
life than she did.

797
00:42:47,046 --> 00:42:49,464
- Oh, God, I hope so.
- You will.

798
00:42:49,632 --> 00:42:54,140
Our kid will be kind and brave
just like you.

799
00:42:54,702 --> 00:42:58,622
♪ <i>I'll keep knocking</i>
<i>on the door...</i> ♪

800
00:42:58,706 --> 00:42:59,804
A baby?

801
00:43:02,417 --> 00:43:05,141
Oh, my God. It's never
gonna be the same again.

802
00:43:05,226 --> 00:43:07,952
No, it's not.
It's going to be better.

803
00:43:10,934 --> 00:43:12,902
♪ <i>You are, you are</i> ♪

804
